DURBAN - A taxi left thirteen people injured on Thursday morning after it rolled on the R56 near Richmond, outside Pietermaritzburg. Russel Meiring of ER24 said when they arrived on scene, they found a taxi lying upright on the side of the road. The commuters had already climbed out of the taxi and were walking around the scene of the accident. “Paramedics assessed the patients and found that a total of thirteen had sustained injuries ranging from minor to moderate. Fortunately, no serious or fatal injuries were reported on this scene,” said Meiring. The injured were treated at the scene and taken to either Greys, Northdale or Edendale Provincial Hospitals. Local authorities were on scene to conduct an investigation into the cause of the accident.. Daily News